Introduction

Correlations

Can you send the correlation between GDP PC and each of the 5 subcomponents of the SPI? And then also send the correlation between the G SPI and each of the 5 subcomponents of the SPI? Along with the 3 main correlations (GDP pc & SPI, GPD pc & G SPI, and SPI & G SPI). So 13 correlations total.

Source: GDP per capita, PPP (current international $) from the World Development Indicatrs (NY.GDP.PCAP.PP.CD). SPI Overall Score from the World Development Indicators. GDP is logged. *** is significant at 0.001 level. ** is significant at 0.01 level. * is significant at 0.05 level. + is significant at 0.01 level.

GDP per capita Correlations

Log GDP per capita & Gender SDG Availability: -0.15+.

Log GDP per capita & SPI Overall Score: 0.67***.

Log GDP per capita & SPI Pillar 1 (Data use) Score: 0.44***.

Log GDP per capita & SPI Pillar 2 (Data services) Score: 0.52***.

Log GDP per capita & SPI Pillar 3 (Data products [Overall SDG Indicator availability]) Score: 0.13+.

Log GDP per capita & SPI Pillar 4 (Data sources) Score: 0.74***.

Log GDP per capita & SPI Pillar 5 (Data infrastructure) Score: 0.71***.

SPI Correlations

Gender SDG Availability & SPI Overall Score: 0.48***.

Gender SDG Availability & SPI Pillar 1 (Data use) Score: 0.53***.

Gender SDG Availability & SPI Pillar 2 (Data services) Score: 0.44***.

Gender SDG Availability & SPI Pillar 3 (Data products [Overall SDG Indicator availability]) Score: 0.69***.

Gender SDG Availability & SPI Pillar 4 (Data sources) Score: 0.34***.

Gender SDG Availability & SPI Pillar 5 (Data infrastructure) Score: 0.25**.
